[1] Malaysia (Sarawak)
Date: 10 Jan 2010
Source: Bernama.com [edited]
<http://bernama.com>


More people in the state were afflicted with dengue fever between last year
[2009] and 2 Jan [2010]. According to a statement from the state health
department here on Sunday [10 Jan 2010], 4579 cases of dengue fever were
reported during the period, compared with 1527 cases in 2008. The Miri
District had the highest at 990, followed by, among others, Kuching
District (838), Sibu (516), Sri Aman (265), and Sarikei (264).

--
